{
  "texts": [
    "Diffusivity is sensitive to the ratio of the orbital radius of its circular trajectory to the obstacle lattice constant as well as the lattice symmetry.",
    "In particular, a CAP can diffuse rapidly in the square lattice but can be caged in the triangular lattice for a long time with the same obstacle packing fraction.",
    "A different CAP can exhibit opposite diffusive behavior in these lattices.",
    "These results reveal a new way to separate chiral particles by passive lattices, in contrast to the traditional sorting methods of ABPs and CAPs by applying an external field 8, 84, 86.",
    "A recent simulation study reported the enhanced diffusivity due to the angular speed heterogeneity of CAPs 68."
  ]
}